## Package/Library Notes

### @react-three/drei

#### IMPORTANT: Html Component

**Correct import**: `import { Html } from '@react-three/drei'`

#### Why this matters
The Html component bridges WebGL and DOM, allowing real HTML elements to be positioned in 3D space.

#### Correct usage
```tsx
<Html 
  position={[x, y, z]} 
  transform 
  occlude={false}
  style={{ pointerEvents: 'auto' }}
>
  <div tabIndex={0} role="button">
    Clickable content
  </div>
</Html>
```

---

### three-stdlib

#### IMPORTANT: Line2 for Fat Lines

**Correct import**: `import { Line2, LineGeometry, LineMaterial } from 'three-stdlib'`

#### Why this matters
Standard Three.js Line has 1px width limit. Line2 supports variable width.

#### Correct usage
```typescript
const geometry = new LineGeometry();
geometry.setPositions([x1, y1, z1, x2, y2, z2]);

const material = new LineMaterial({
  color: 0x3b82f6,
  linewidth: 2,
  resolution: new Vector2(window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight)
});
```

